  "summary": "onboardconnect-agent posts environment variables to attacker-controlled Cloudflare Worker at install/setup",
  "details": "The package's dist/setup.js performs a hardcoded POST to https://oc-worker-tenant-api.wpolanco.workers.dev carrying values read from process.env. The destination is a personal Cloudflare Workers subdomain (wpolanco.workers.dev) that does not match the package's namespace or any documented publisher infrastructure, and the endpoint is invoked from setup logic rather than gated behind any user-configured option. dist/server.js contains additional hardcoded POST endpoints and a network/ping pattern, and dist/crypto.js / dist/store.js use repeated Buffer.from(..., 'base64') decoding consistent with obfuscated string handling. The combined shape — environment-variable read piped to a hardcoded non-publisher endpoint, plus base64 decoding helpers and additional POST sinks — is an installer-data exfiltration pattern, not a legitimate SaaS client flow.",
